** STEP 1: git clone GOTM and GETM *************************
Regarding our iow codes please try out the following. If I registered your IP and ssh key correctly the "git remote add" commands should work...
 
#clone official getm
git clone git://git.code.sf.net/p/getm/code
cd code
 
#checkout "official" iow branch
git checkout -b iow origin/iow
 
#add iow repository
git remote add -f iow gitolite@svn.io-warnemuende.de:getm-iow
 
#checkout "extended" iow branch (requires gotm-iow)
git checkout -b iow_master iow/master
 
 
#similar for gotm
git clone git://github.com/gotm-model/code.git
cd code
git remote add -f iow gitolite@svn.io-warnemuende.de:gotm-iow
git checkout -b iow_master iow/master


** STEP 2: git clone FABM  *****************
See https://github.com/fabm-model/fabm/wiki/GOTM

git clone https://github.com/fabm-model/fabm.git


** STEP 3: compile gotm ************************************
See https://github.com/fabm-model/fabm/wiki/GOTM

To build GOTM with FABM support, make sure you have CMake 2.8.8 or higher and a supported Fortran compiler. Then follow our platform-specific instructions for running CMake; you need to specify <GOTMDIR>/src as the source directory and set option FABM_BASE to <FABMDIR>. Here, <GOTMDIR> is the directory with GOTM source code and <FABMDIR> is the directory with FABM source code.
On Linux-like systems, building is typically achieved by executing something like:
mkdir -p ~/build/gotm && cd ~/build/gotm
cmake <GOTMDIR>/src -DFABM_BASE=<FABMDIR>
make install
This will produce a GOTM executable at ~/local/gotm/bin/gotm.


** STEP 4: compile getm ************************************
see partly https://www.io-warnemuende.de/getm/articles/getm.html

-Adapt the file getm-git/code/scripts/linux/getm_configure.sh
-I've stuck this in: /home/jvandermolen/tools/getm/build
-run this
-in directory /home/jvandermolen/tools/getm/build/ifort, create a link dimensions.h to the dimensions.h of the desired setup
-do: make install in the destination directory of the script (/home/jvandermolen/tools/getm/build/ifort)




##############################################################3
To check out other branches:

** bottom friction branch (12 branches ahead master):
cd $GOTMDIR
git checkout master
cd $GETMDIR
git fetch iow
git checkout -b bottfric iow/knut/bottfric

** ip branch (7 branches ahead master):
cd $GETMDIR
git fetch iow
git checkout -b ip iow/knut/ip

** les branch (before ip)
cd $GETMDIR
git fetch iow
git checkout -b les iow/knut/les


To switch branches:
git checkout les



NOTE: for master, the executable has a different name, see comments in compile script
